{"title_page": "Dmitry Shevchenko (fencer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Dmitriy Shevchenko\n| birth_name     = \n| full_name      = Dmitriy Stepanovich Shevchenko\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = \n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1967|11|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Moscow]], [[Russian SFSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| website        = \n| country        = \n| sport          = [[Fencing]]\n| event          = [[Foil (fencing)|Foil]]\n| collegeteam    = \n| club           = \n| team           = \n| turnedpro      = \n| coach          = \n| retired        = \n| coaching       = \n| worlds         = \n| regionals      = \n| nationals      = \n| olympics       = \n| paralympics    = \n| highestranking = \n| pb             = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Men's [[fencing]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{RUS}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1996 Summer Olympics|1996 Atlanta]] | [[Fencing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|Team foil]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Fencing at the 2000 Summer Olympics|Individual  foil]]}}\n| show-medals    = yes\n}}\n\n'''Dmitriy Stepanovich Shevchenko''' (also spelled Chevtchenko, {{lang-ru|\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0428\u0435\u0432\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e}}, born 13 November 1967 in [[Moscow]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[fencing|fencer]], who won a gold Olympic medal in the team foil competition at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta]] and bronze Olympic medal in the individual foil competition at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]].<ref name=\"databaseolympics\">{{cite web|url=http://www.databaseolympics.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=SHEVCDMI01 |title=Dmitry Shevchenko |accessdate=28 December 2011 |website=databaseOlympics.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026102911/http://www.databaseolympics.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=SHEVCDMI01 |archivedate=26 October 2012 }}</ref><ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/sh/dmitry-shevchenko-1.html |title=Dmitry Shevchenko |accessdate=28 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IOC profile|dimitri-shevshenko|Dimitri Shevshenko}}\n* {{Olympic Channel|dmitri-shevchenko|Dmitri Shevchenko}}\n* {{FIE|1195|Dmitriy Shevchenko}}\n* {{EFC|00690282|Dimitri Chevtchenko}}\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Fencing Team Foil Men}}\n{{World Champions in Men's Foil}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shevchenko, Dmitry}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Moscow]]\n[[Category:Soviet male fencers]]\n[[Category:Russian male fencers]]\n[[Category:Fencers at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Fencers at the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Fencers at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic fencers of the Unified Team]]\n[[Category:Olympic fencers of Russia]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Russia]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Russia]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in fencing]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Universiade medalists in fencing]]\n[[Category:Universiade gold medalists for the Soviet Union]]\n\n\n{{Russia-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n{{russia-fencing-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Dmitriy Shevchenko\n| birth_name     = \n| full_name      = Dmitriy Stepanovich Shevchenko\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = \n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1967|11|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Moscow]], [[Russian SFSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| website        = \n| country        = \n| sport          = [[Fencing]]\n| event          = [[Foil (fencing)|Foil]]\n| collegeteam    = \n| club           = \n| team           = \n| turnedpro      = \n| coach          = \n| retired        = \n| coaching       = \n| worlds         = \n| regionals      = \n| nationals      = \n| olympics       = \n| paralympics    = \n| highestranking = \n| pb             = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Men's [[fencing]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{RUS}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1996 Summer Olympics|1996 Atlanta]] | [[Fencing at the 1996 Summer Olympics|Team foil]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Fencing at the 2000 Summer Olympics|Individual  foil]]}}\n| show-medals    = yes\n}}\n\n'''Dmitriy Stepanovich Shevchenko''' (also spelled Chevtchenko, {{lang-ru|\u0414\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0421\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0428\u0435\u0432\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e}}, born 13 November 1967 in [[Moscow]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[fencing|fencer]], who won a gold Olympic medal in the team foil competition at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta]] and bronze Olympic medal in the individual foil competition at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]].<ref name=\"databaseolympics\">{{cite web|url=http://www.databaseolympics.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=SHEVCDMI01 |title=Dmitry Shevchenko |accessdate=28 December 2011 |website=databaseOlympics.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026102911/http://www.databaseolympics.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=SHEVCDMI01 |archivedate=26 October 2012 }}</ref><ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/sh/dmitry-shevchenko-1.html |title=Dmitry Shevchenko |accessdate=28 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{I